items.title: Scheduler: can't delete/create job because client seems to be 'str'

labels.name: api: cloudscheduler
labels.description: Issues related to the Cloud Scheduler API.

labels.name: type: question
labels.description: Request for information or clarification. Not an issue.

items.body:
Hello

When I try to create or delete a job the client don't recognize the mode create, delete, ....

#### Environment details
1. Scheduler
2. Windows 10
3. Python version and virtual environment information: Python 3.7.3
4. google-cloud-scheduler-1.2.1


#### Code example

```
from google.cloud import scheduler_v1
import logging

client = scheduler_v1.CloudSchedulerClient()
name = client.job_path(GCP_PROJECT, "europe-west6", "test")
client.delete_job(name)
```

#### Stack trace
```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "C:\Users\C203580\.conda\envs\gcp_onboarding\lib\site-packages\IPython\core\interactiveshell.py", line 3331, in run_code
    exec(code_obj, self.user_global_ns, self.user_ns)
  File "<ipython-input-28-26eba677eb8b>", line 1, in <module>
    client.delete_job(name)
  File "C:\Users\C203580\.conda\envs\gcp_onboarding\lib\site-packages\google\cloud\scheduler_v1\gapic\cloud_scheduler_client.py", line 621, in delete_job
    self.transport.delete_job,
AttributeError: 'str' object has no attribute 'delete_job'

```

Cheers
Davide
